LAFIA – Nasarawa state chapter of the rice producers, processors, Millers And Marketers Association Of Nigeria (NARPPMMAN), on Tuesday said the association will sustain its core mandate to increase rice production, attract investment, encourage local consumption and patronage and improve the capacity of all actors. Abel Jilemsam, the State chairman of the Association disclosed this in Lafia, the state capital, at the inauguration of the local government exco of the association. He explained that NARPPMMAN will remain competitive locally and internationally and draw the government’s attention to the challenges faced by value chain players and attract funding from government, private financiers and partners international organizations directly involved in rice value chain. Abel, described NARPPMMAN as the new hub in the agricultural sector aimed at showcasing all the potentials in rice chain, Jilemsam appealed to members to join to develop modern agriculture as the association has alot to offer. According to him,” As an organization in the rice value chain, we are determined to harmonize our experiences in all areas of success and challenges to build massively to move rice commodity to an enviable stage to create the desired impact on the link between the value chain players from down to upstream” “This will create specialization among the actors, make the operational structures seamless as well as create access to sustainable funding, structured market, fair pricing and a guaranteed off-take”; Jilemsam said.Nuhu Oshafu, the Nasarawa state Commissioner for Agriculture and water resources who was represented by the permanent secretary of the ministry, Nuhu Usman Bunu, at the occasion congratulated the members for coming under one umbrella for the purpose of rice production. The Commissioner assured NARPPMMAN that the Nasarawa state government will continue to seek areas of collaboration with the association and appealed for a more robust network.In his remark, the National President of the Association, Mustafa Ahmadu, represented by the vice-chairman in charge of North-Central, Ishaku Samaila, appreciated President Muhammadu Buhari for encouraging rice farmers for optimal production. The national chairman also appreciated the Nasarawa state governor Engr. Abdullahi Sule for the support given to the association and requested more support from the state government.